node.title: Foo Fighters Perform Under a Blue Whale
node.alt: At the American Museum of Natural History gala, the Foo Fighters performed.Â
node.description: And New York Public Radio honors Radiolab at its dinner gala.
node.content: ["The American Museum of Natural History raised about $3 million at its annual fall gala on Nov. 18, with 450 guests dining under the big blue whale in the Hall of Ocean Life. As usual, there was a large contingent of \u201cSaturday Night Live\u201d cast members. (Lorne Michaels, the show\u2019s longtime producer, sits on the museum\u2019s board.) And New York Public Radio held its annual gala on Nov. 16 at the Plaza Hotel; the Radiolab podcast, now in its 20th year, was honored."]
